            <section data-scroll-reveal="enter from-left">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-700 mb-4">Discover the Shape of Your Sheep: Unlocking the Art of Leadership</h2>
                <br>
                <p>What if I told you that 70% of employees feel disengaged at work? It’s a staggering number, and it’s not just a statistic—it’s a wake-up call. In <em>The Way of the Shepherd</em>, Dr. Kevin Leman and William Pentak reveal a timeless truth: great leadership isn’t about managing tasks; it’s about understanding people. And that starts with discovering the shape of your sheep.</p>
                <br>
                <p>Yes, your sheep. Think of your team as a flock—each member unique, with their own strengths, quirks, and needs. The best leaders don’t herd blindly; they take the time to truly know their people. As the book puts it, <strong>“You can’t lead sheep you don’t know.”</strong> It’s a simple yet profound idea that transforms how we approach leadership.</p>
                <br>
                <p>So, how do you uncover the shape of your sheep? It starts with intentional observation, meaningful conversations, and a willingness to adapt your leadership style. This isn’t about micromanaging or coddling—it’s about empowering your team to thrive by meeting them where they are.</p>
                <br>
                <p>In this article, we’ll dive into actionable strategies to help you discover the shape of your sheep, from identifying individual strengths to creating an environment where everyone feels valued. Whether you’re a seasoned leader or just stepping into a management role, these insights will help you build a stronger, more engaged team.</p>
                <br>
                <p>Ready to transform your leadership approach? Let’s get started. Because when you know the shape of your sheep, you don’t just lead—you inspire.</p>
            </section>

