            <!-- Section 2: Actionable Strategies -->
            <section data-scroll-reveal="enter from-right">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-700 mb-4">How to Discover the Shape of Your Sheep</h2>
                <br>
                <p>Discovering the shape of your sheep is about understanding your team members as individuals. Here are actionable strategies to help you get started:</p>
                <br>
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-600 mb-3">1. Observe and Listen</h3>
                <p>Great leaders are keen observers. Pay attention to how your team members work, communicate, and interact with others. Listen actively during conversations—what excites them? What challenges do they face? This will help you identify their unique strengths and motivations.</p>
                <br>
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-600 mb-3">2. Have Meaningful One-on-Ones</h3>
                <p>Regular one-on-one meetings are a powerful way to build trust and understand your team members better. Ask open-ended questions like, “What do you enjoy most about your work?” or “Where do you feel you can grow?” These conversations reveal insights into their aspirations and concerns.</p>
                <br>
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-600 mb-3">3. Adapt Your Leadership Style</h3>
                <p>Not everyone responds to the same leadership approach. Some team members thrive with autonomy, while others need more guidance. Tailor your leadership style to meet the needs of each individual, ensuring they feel supported and valued.</p>
                <br>
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-600 mb-3">4. Create a Safe Environment</h3>
                <p>Your team should feel safe to express their ideas, ask questions, and make mistakes. Foster a culture of openness and trust, where everyone feels comfortable being themselves. This encourages authenticity and innovation.</p>
                <br>
                <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-600 mb-3">5. Celebrate Individuality</h3>
                <p>Recognize and celebrate the unique contributions of each team member. Whether it’s a shout-out in a team meeting or a personalized note of appreciation, acknowledging their efforts boosts morale and reinforces their value to the team.</p>
            </section>

            <!-- Section 3: Key Takeaways -->
            <section data-scroll-reveal="enter from-left">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-green-700 mb-4">Key Takeaways</h2>
                <br>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
                    <li><strong>Know Your Sheep:</strong> Leadership starts with understanding your team members as individuals.</li>
                    <li><strong>Lead with Intentionality:</strong> Be deliberate in your actions and decisions, always considering the impact on your team.</li>
                    <li><strong>Empower Your Flock:</strong> Provide the tools, support, and environment your team needs to succeed.</li>
                    <li><strong>Build Trust:</strong> Trust is the foundation of strong leadership. Be consistent, transparent, and reliable.</li>
                    <li><strong>Inspire Growth:</strong> Encourage your team to grow both personally and professionally, and lead by example.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

